'''[[Capital punishment]]''' is a legal penalty in the '''[[Saint Kitts and Nevis|Federation of St. Kitts and Nevis]]''', and is carried out by [[hanging]]. The death penalty can only be applied for aggravated murder and treason.<ref>http://www.theadvocatesforhumanrights.org/uploads/st_kitts_and_nevis_hrc_dp_march_2015.pdf</ref>

Since gaining its sovereignty in 1983, St. Kitts and Nevis has executed only three individuals, with its most recent execution being carried out in 2008, when [[Charles Laplace]] was hanged for murdering his wife.<ref name="CSMonitor">{{Cite news |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Asia-South-Central/2012/0829/India-uses-death-penalty-5-other-places-where-it-s-legal-but-rare/St.-Kitts-and-Nevis |title=India uses death penalty: 5 other places where it's legal but rare |last=Bright |first=Arthur |date=August 29, 2012 |access-date=May 21, 2017 |publisher=The Christian Science Monitor}}</ref> As of 2016, the country has just one death row inmate.<ref>{{cite web|title= Death sentences and executions in 2016|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/documents/act50/5740/2017/en/ |publisher= amnesty.org |accessdate=August 21, 2017}}</ref>

St. Kitts and Nevis voted against the [[United Nations moratorium on the death penalty]] in 2007, 2008, 2010, 2012, 2014, and 2016.

