[[File:Richard Buchta - Portrait of a Zande (Makaraka) warrior.jpg|thumb|Portrait of a Zande (Makaraka) warrior]]
'''Makaraka''' (also, '''Iddio''' or '''Adio''') are an ethnic group indigenous to [[Central Africa]], closely related to the powerful [[Azande]] or NiamNiam, occupying the [[Bahr el Ghazal (region of South Sudan)|Bahr-el-Ghazal]] west of [[Lado, South Sudan|Lado]]. They came originally from the country of the [[Kibas]], north of the [[Welle River]]. They do not extract the incisors.<ref>{{EB1911 |wstitle=Makaraka |volume=17 |page=451 |inline=1}}</ref>  Currently, they form part of the population of the [[South Sudan]]ese state of [[Central Equatoria]].

